Ask HN: How big companies handle big queues?
text:
I would like to know how big companies handle big queues. For example, if there are 1M users and each sends one message and it all happens almost at the same time within few seconds timeframe.

It means 1M messages need to reach other 1M users and 1M push notifications need to be sent. I presume all those requests go to the queue so the response is returned faster and user experience is better.

But how do those companies handle 1M queue jobs, since most of those messages need to reach other users almost in realtime, without much delay.

Ask HN: Parquet Outside Spark?
text: The Parquet file format (which is used by Spark and Hadoop) has column storage, stored complex nested data etc.  I find a need to read these, and was surprised to find a lack of support in terms of libraries (in Debian for example).  Is this format just not used much outside Spark & friends, so not much demand?  Or some dark reason that the common Linux distros don't want to include it?

Ask HN: Is there a good Java course for absolute beginners?
text:
My girlfriend is in the field of genetics and cardiovascular sciences. She's considering a career change into programming. I've spent some time looking at free and some paid courses online, I've checked content on coursera/udemy/linkedin learning/o'reilly. It seems to me that all these courses are either someone trying to make a quick $ with minimum effort or they are targeted at people with some CS knowledge who just want to pick-up a new language.

Is there a free or paid course that is designed for a complete beginner programmers and teaches them using Java specifically. A course which gives enough exercises at each small step and support.

I need help to improve the release process
text:
Hi everyone,
I recently took a position as a CTO and I've been enjoying my time while improving the work the team has been making.
My biggest struggle right now is how to better release features in production, the team doesn't have a standardized way of releasing features into production and the sales and marketing teams never find out when things are release.
I tried to implement release notes but I'm still struggling with the releases because I never know what's ready to be released and what's still on QA process.
I've asked the team for their help but I don't think they know what to do.
Could someone point me towards the right direction of improving this process?
Thanks!
